{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2013}}
'''Vladimir Kojève''', or '''Khodzhev''', was a Russian [[major-general]] who acted as a military advisor to the government of [[Syria]].<ref>{{cite news|title=CONFIRMED: A Top Russian General Was Killed By Syrian Rebels While Advising Assad|url=http://www.businessinsider.com/russian-general-killed-by-syrian-rebels-2012-10|accessdate=3 October 2012|newspaper=Business Insider|date=3 October 2012}}</ref>  He was allegedly killed in the [[Syrian civil war]]. In October 2012, after his death, personal documents were published by [[Al Arabiya]] which suggested he was working as part of a contract under which the Russian government provided security assistance to the [[Bashar Assad|Assad]] regime; documents suggested he had access to all security facilities in Syria.<ref>{{cite news|title=Leaks confirm death of top Russian general in Syria|url=http://english.alarabiya.net/articles/2012/10/03/241644.html|accessdate=3 October 2012|newspaper=Al Arabiya|date=3 October 2012}}</ref>

However, [[Now Lebanon]] cast doubt on the authenticity of [[Al Arabiya]]'s story.<ref>{{cite news|title=Russian military officer killed in Syria, Al-Arabiya "leaked" docs show|url=http://www.nowlebanon.com/NewsArticleDetails.aspx?ID=442776|accessdate=3 October 2012|date=3 October 2012}}</ref> Kuzheyev had earlier appeared on television, in August 2012, to deny reports of his death.<ref>{{cite news|title=Russian general denies reports he was killed by Free Syrian Army|url=http://english.alarabiya.net/articles/2012/08/08/231005.html|accessdate=3 October 2012|newspaper=Al Arabiya|date=8 August 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121001031601/http://english.alarabiya.net/articles/2012/08/08/231005.html|archive-date=1 October 2012|dead-url=yes|df=dmy-all}}</ref>

